snippet.textDisplay: To all... I think Lalon Fakir rebelled against the various atrocities and dogmas of the erstwhile Bengal. His songs and/or thoughts are philosophies whose meanings are deep and can be easily not understood by a person. I guess that's why we are more interested in saying this song is bad and its a crime to make a fusion. But my request to you all is listen to the essence and you will find what Lalon said and its truly beautiful. and as far as India and Bangladesh goes, my ancestors are from Bangladesh and they are still there. But because of this man-made borders we are apart. But music do not have any boundaries, cannot be suppressed or muted... many a times many scholars, free thinkers, philosophers have pit their thoughts in music and conveyed their message... that's why we Love Rabindrasangeet... they teach us about life... they teach us that we must be free thinkers and not suppress anyone... Then the whole struggle and work of Lalon Fakir go to waste. Ei gaan jamon akjon Banglabhashi bujhbe tamon-i akjon Hindibhaashio bujhbe. akjon Hindibhaashi ke akrishto korbe Bangla shekhar jaatay shey aro bhalo kore bujhtay paaray... ami nijay amon onek Hindibhaashi ke jani je Banglabhaasha ke mon thheke bhalobashe r shroddha kore... taara bolay amar ebong amader ei Banglabhaasha khub shrutimodhur... mon ke unmukto kore amrao to ato ohetuk baje comment na kore ei gaantar muul maanay bojhar cheshta korte pari... akta kotha bhola uchit noi... akshomoy ei Bangla kintu unified India-r mostishko chhilo... r ei gaan kn2 shetai tulay dhorche, amar motay... This is just my personal opinion...

But my request to you all is listen to the essence and you will find what Lalon said and its truly beautiful. and as far as India and Bangladesh goes, my ancestors are from Bangladesh and they are still there. But because of this man-made borders we are apart. But music do not have any boundaries, cannot be suppressed or muted... many a times many scholars, free thinkers, philosophers have pit their thoughts in music and conveyed their message... that's why we Love Rabindrasangeet... they teach us about life... they teach us that we must be free thinkers and not suppress anyone... Then the whole struggle and work of Lalon Fakir go to waste. Ei gaan jamon akjon Banglabhashi bujhbe tamon-i akjon Hindibhaashio bujhbe. akjon Hindibhaashi ke akrishto korbe Bangla shekhar jaatay shey aro bhalo kore bujhtay paaray... ami nijay amon onek Hindibhaashi ke jani je Banglabhaasha ke mon thheke bhalobashe r shroddha kore... taara bolay amar ebong amader ei Banglabhaasha khub shrutimodhur... mon ke unmukto kore amrao to ato ohetuk baje comment na kore ei gaantar muul maanay bojhar cheshta korte pari... akta kotha bhola uchit noi... akshomoy ei Bangla kintu unified India-r mostishko chhilo... r ei gaan kn2 shetai tulay dhorche, amar motay... This is just my personal opinion...
